FBIS4-35327 "drnes104_j_94042" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 29 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen `Source' Denies Aden Proposed Unconditional Cease-Fire `Source' Denies Aden Proposed Unconditional Cease-Fire LD2905120694 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 1000 GMT 29 May 94 LD2905120694 Kuwait Radio Kuwait Arabic BFN [Text] Aden radio broadcast a statement this morning by a responsible source in the Democratic Republic of Yemen -- which has been declared in the south -- denying Sanaa's assertion that officials in the Yemeni Socialist Party have proposed an unconditional cease-fire in Yemen. The source declared that Aden insists on two basic conditions for a cease-fire. These are the withdrawal of all northern forces to positions behind the previous borders between the two parts of Yemen, and the holding of direct talks with the Aden government.
